---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
	title="About this site — Marc Krevitz"
	description="How this site was built, and what it's built with."
>
	<article class="article">
		<a class="back-link" href="/">← Back home</a>
		<header>
			<span class="mono">Meta</span>
			<h1 class="article-title">About this site</h1>
		</header>

		<div class="prose">
			<p>
				This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>, a framework built for
				content-heavy sites like this one. Pages ship as plain HTML and CSS — there's no
				client-side framework running in the background, so there's very little for a visitor's
				browser to load.
			</p>
			<p>
				Furniture, Tech Projects, and Work entries are Astro <strong>content collections</strong>:
				each post is a single Markdown file with a little front-matter (title, date, category).
				Adding a new post means writing a Markdown file, not touching any code.
			</p>
			<p>
				The design is hand-built to match an approved mockup — no page-builder or template.
				Type is set in <a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/IBM+Plex+Sans">IBM Plex Sans</a> and <a href="https://fonts.google.com/specimen/IBM+Plex+Mono">IBM Plex Mono</a>.
			</p>
			<p>
				It's hosted on <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/">Cloudflare</a> (Workers static assets), auto-deploying from a <a href="https://github.com/MarcRK/marc-krevitz-site">GitHub repo</a> on every push.
				The domain is registered through Cloudflare too. The contact form is
				handled by <a href="https://formspree.io">Formspree</a>, since a static site has no
				server of its own to receive form submissions.
			</p>
			<p>
				I built it with <a href="https://claude.com/claude-code">Claude Code</a>, Anthropic's AI
				coding assistant — pairing on everything from the initial scaffold to deploy
				configuration and content structure.
			</p>
		</div>
	</article>
</Layout>
